    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down, Beckenham, Kent,</placeName>
                    <date>Aug. 21, 1881.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I much regret that I cannot comply with your wishes. I have made it a rule (which I have rarely broken) never to write in Periodicals, because I am unable to write short articles in an interesting manner, &amp; it would consume much of my time.</p>
                    <p>Thanking you for your courteous note, &amp; wishing continued success to your excellent Journal,<ref target="#foot.f1"/> I remain Dear Sir Yours faithfully Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The note has not been found; the journal has not been identified. CD used similar wording in declining an invitation to write for <hi rend="italic">Kosmos</hi> (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 27, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-12063.xml">letter to Ernst Krause, 27 May 1879</ref>).</note>
    
        </div>
    
